sudo apt update
sudo apt install enum4linux -y

git clone https://github.com/cddmp/enum4linux-ng.git
cd enum4linux-ng
pip3 install -r requirements.txt


Basic Usage 
enum4linux -a <target>

Sample: 

# Full enumeration on the target machine
enum4linux -a 192.168.94.140


Shortened Output:
 ========================================= 
|    Target Information Gathering        |
 ========================================= 

[+] Server Operating System: Windows Server 2016
[+] NetBIOS Name: WIN-SERVER
[+] NetBIOS Domain: WORKGROUP
[+] DNS Domain: win.local
[+] Users found:
    Administrator
    Guest
    john
    alice

[+] Shares found:
    IPC$
    ADMIN$
    SharedDocs

[+] Password Policy:
    - Min Password Length: 6
    - Password History Length: 24

Common Flags:

Flag	Description
-a	Run all enumeration options
-u <user>	Provide a username
-p <pass>	Provide a password
-U	Enumerate users
-S	Enumerate shares
-G	Enumerate groups
-P	Enumerate password policies
-o	OS information
-r	RID cycling (default range 500â€“550)
-R	Reverse lookup for hosts in a range

